ğŸ“‚ backup.sh (Backup-skript / Backup Script)
Svenska:
Detta skript skapar en sÃ¤kerhetskopia av filer med en viss filtillÃ¤ggstyp inom anvÃ¤ndarens hemkatalog. Det Ã¤r anvÃ¤ndbart fÃ¶r att sÃ¤kerstÃ¤lla att viktiga filer inte gÃ¥r fÃ¶rlorade. Jag har lÃ¤rt mig hur man anvÃ¤nder find-kommandot fÃ¶r att sÃ¶ka efter filer och cp fÃ¶r att kopiera dem.

English:
This script creates a backup of files with a certain extension type within the user's home directory. It is useful for ensuring that important files are not lost. I've learned how to use the find command to search for files and cp to copy them.

Kodexempel / Code Example:


#!/bin/bash
# Backup Script
# Author: kjn

echo "ğŸ“‚ Backup Script"
echo "============================="
echo "This script backs up files of a specific type."
echo "Files are searched in your home directory and can only be saved within \\$HOME."

echo "ğŸ” Enter file extension (e.g., .sh, .txt, .jpg)"
read -p "File type: " files_suffix

# Validate input
if [[ -z "\$files_suffix" ]]; then
    echo "âŒ No file extension provided. Exiting..."
    exit 1
fi

echo "ğŸ“‚ Enter the backup directory"
read -p "Backup directory: " dir_name

# Check if the directory name is empty
if [[ -z "\$dir_name" ]]; then
    echo "âŒ No directory provided. Exiting..."
    exit 1
fi

# Check if the directory exists, create it if not
if [ ! -d "\$dir_name" ]; then
    echo "Backup directory does not exist. Creating the directory..."
    mkdir -p "\$dir_name"
fi

# Create the backup
echo "Searching for files with the extension \$files_suffix..."
find \$HOME -type f -name "*\$files_suffix" -exec cp {} \$dir_name \;

echo "âœ… Backup completed. Files saved to \$dir_name."
Viktigaste Funktioner / Key Features:

AnvÃ¤ndaren anger filtillÃ¤gg och mÃ¥lkatalog / User specifies file extension and target directory
Skriptet sÃ¶ker och kopierar filer inom $HOME / The script searches and copies files within $HOME
GrundlÃ¤ggande validering fÃ¶r att fÃ¶rhindra fel / Basic validation to prevent errors
AnvÃ¤ndbarhet / Usefulness:

SÃ¤kerstÃ¤ller att viktiga filer backas upp regelbundet.
LÃ¤r ut hur man anvÃ¤nder find och cp fÃ¶r filhantering i Bash.
AnvÃ¤ndningsexempel / Usage Example:


./backup.sh
# Output: ğŸ” Enter file extension (e.g., .sh, .txt, .jpg)
# Input: .txt
# Output: ğŸ“‚ Enter the backup directory
# Input: /path/to/backup
# Output: Searching for files with the extension .txt...
# Output: âœ… Backup completed. Files saved to /path/to/backup
